1
00:00:29,396 --> 00:00:30,476
Hurricane Gabriel...

2
00:00:30,516 --> 00:00:32,836
continues to pound
the eastern seaboard.

3
00:00:32,876 --> 00:00:36,716
It has now been upgraded
to a category 4 hurricane.

4
00:00:42,516 --> 00:00:43,636
Forecasters are predicting...

5
00:00:43,716 --> 00:00:46,316
major damage
and severe flooding...

6
00:00:46,356 --> 00:00:48,556
which we are already seeing
in many parts...

7
00:00:48,596 --> 00:00:49,756
Later, we go live...

8
00:00:49,796 --> 00:00:52,236
to a tense scene
some 300 miles north...

9
00:00:52,276 --> 00:00:53,876
where evacuees battle...

10
00:00:53,916 --> 00:00:55,516
to stock up on food and water.

11
00:00:55,556 --> 00:00:57,356
But first, the latest...

12
00:00:57,396 --> 00:01:00,316
...for desperately needed
medical aid.

13
00:01:01,276 --> 00:01:05,116
-City Of Ghosts-

14
00:01:38,876 --> 00:01:40,156
Here at Gibraltar Point...

15
00:01:40,196 --> 00:01:42,516
we have reports
of entire communities...

16
00:01:42,556 --> 00:01:44,196
being leveled.

17
00:01:44,236 --> 00:01:47,836
Gusts as strong as
150 miles per hour...

18
00:01:47,916 --> 00:01:49,796
strong enough to level homes.

19
00:01:49,876 --> 00:01:52,716
Scores of residents
have heeded the call...

20
00:01:52,756 --> 00:01:54,556
and have been
pouring into the shelter...

21
00:01:54,596 --> 00:01:56,796
here at Gibraltar Point
all night.

22
00:01:56,836 --> 00:01:58,636
The big concern for them is...

23
00:01:58,676 --> 00:02:00,836
will they have a home
to return to?

24
00:02:00,876 --> 00:02:02,396
I don't know
what to expect to find...

25
00:02:02,436 --> 00:02:04,036
when I get back there...

26
00:02:04,076 --> 00:02:08,076
but I'm sure we'll be talking
with the insurance company.

27
00:02:08,116 --> 00:02:10,756
Well, we do have insurance,
thank God.

28
00:02:10,796 --> 00:02:12,556
I expect it'll take time...

29
00:02:12,596 --> 00:02:14,956
but, you know, eventually,
we'll have our house back.

30
00:02:14,956 --> 00:02:17,436
We've got insurance, so...

31
00:02:17,516 --> 00:02:18,796
The governor
of North Carolina...

32
00:02:18,876 --> 00:02:21,476
has declared a state
of emergency in several...

33
00:02:34,516 --> 00:02:36,116
Jimmy, we've got a real
mess on our hands.

34
00:02:36,156 --> 00:02:37,556
I've been trying
to contact Mr. Nagel.

35
00:02:37,596 --> 00:02:39,436
Jimmy Cremmins?

36
00:02:39,436 --> 00:02:41,396
Yeah, I am.

37
00:02:41,436 --> 00:02:42,636
What's going on here?

38
00:02:42,676 --> 00:02:43,996
I'm Agent Burden
with the F.B.I.

39
00:02:44,036 --> 00:02:46,196
This is Agent Philips.
Can we have a word with you?

40
00:02:46,236 --> 00:02:47,356
Sure.

41
00:02:48,876 --> 00:02:49,916
Who's supposed
to be in charge...

42
00:02:49,996 --> 00:02:51,076
of business operations?

43
00:02:51,116 --> 00:02:52,196
Mr. Nagel.

44
00:02:52,236 --> 00:02:54,556
Do you have any idea
where we might find him?

45
00:02:54,596 --> 00:02:56,996
He was based overseas.

46
00:02:57,076 --> 00:02:58,156
He called nearly every day.

47
00:02:58,196 --> 00:03:00,036
I just never--

48
00:03:00,076 --> 00:03:02,076
I never met him in person.

49
00:03:03,116 --> 00:03:04,476
We'll need you
to come down to the office...

50
00:03:04,516 --> 00:03:06,596
to answer a few more questions.

51
00:03:08,596 --> 00:03:10,956
Let's go over it one more time.

52
00:03:12,116 --> 00:03:13,996
I answered an ad...

53
00:03:14,036 --> 00:03:15,596
in "The Tribune."

54
00:03:15,636 --> 00:03:19,076
Capable Trust was looking
to fill some positions for...

55
00:03:20,636 --> 00:03:22,756
North American
headquarters, and...

56
00:03:22,836 --> 00:03:24,796
Well, they hired the right guy.

57
00:03:24,876 --> 00:03:26,596
You're a hell
of a salesman, Jimmy.

58
00:03:26,636 --> 00:03:28,196
Were there any other
offshore accounts...

59
00:03:28,236 --> 00:03:30,636
besides the ones in
Zurich and the Caymans?

60
00:03:30,676 --> 00:03:31,916
No. Not to my knowledge.

61
00:03:31,956 --> 00:03:34,796
So they were the accounts you
would draw from to pay claims.

62
00:03:34,836 --> 00:03:36,276
Right.

63
00:03:36,316 --> 00:03:37,516
It's gonna be tough
to pay those claims, Jimmy.

64
00:03:38,516 --> 00:03:40,036
Those accounts are empty.

65
00:03:41,676 --> 00:03:43,076
It's not your fault,
of course...

66
00:03:43,116 --> 00:03:45,196
but it is a shame.

67
00:03:45,236 --> 00:03:47,916
All those innocent people
lost their homes.

68
00:03:47,956 --> 00:03:49,076
And you have no idea...

69
00:03:49,116 --> 00:03:50,996
where we can find
this Mr. Nagel?

70
00:03:52,636 --> 00:03:54,756
Don't you want
to help us, Jimmy?

71
00:03:54,796 --> 00:03:56,836
What do you think?

72
00:03:56,916 --> 00:03:57,956
Of course I do.

73
00:04:00,916 --> 00:04:04,196
Mr. Nagel--
the name keeps coming up.

74
00:04:04,236 --> 00:04:06,836
He wasn't lying.
I ran a check.

75
00:04:06,876 --> 00:04:08,916
There was an ad in "The Tribune"
classified section...

76
00:04:08,956 --> 00:04:11,396
Iast September.
What do you think?

77
00:04:11,436 --> 00:04:12,956
It's a sophisticated
Ponzi scheme...

78
00:04:12,996 --> 00:04:15,716
Iike that outfit operating
out of Belgium last year...

79
00:04:15,756 --> 00:04:17,036
selling disaster insurance...

80
00:04:17,076 --> 00:04:19,076
with no intention
of paying any claims.

81
00:04:19,116 --> 00:04:21,956
I bet the farm this guy
is connected somehow.

82
00:04:21,996 --> 00:04:23,996
We just got to keep on digging.

83
00:04:24,036 --> 00:04:25,836
Collect call
from United States...

84
00:04:25,916 --> 00:04:26,956
from Jimmy.

85
00:04:27,036 --> 00:04:29,476
I accept. Jimmy, it's Kaspar.

86
00:04:29,516 --> 00:04:30,996
Listen.

87
00:04:31,076 --> 00:04:33,196
I need to talk to him now.

88
00:04:33,236 --> 00:04:34,316
He's unreachable.

89
00:04:34,356 --> 00:04:36,156
He's not in Bangkok.
He's not in town.

90
00:04:36,196 --> 00:04:38,196
He's not in Ba...

91
00:04:38,236 --> 00:04:39,476
Well, where is he?

92
00:04:39,516 --> 00:04:41,356
Cambodia. That's all I know.

93
00:04:41,396 --> 00:04:43,796
But he's supposed to call in.
Perhaps I can help.

94
00:04:44,756 --> 00:04:45,996
Cambodia?

95
00:04:58,956 --> 00:05:00,196
Well...

96
00:05:00,236 --> 00:05:01,676
we ran a check on you.

97
00:05:02,956 --> 00:05:04,396
You came up clean.

98
00:05:05,676 --> 00:05:08,516
We're sorry you had
to go through all this...

99
00:05:08,556 --> 00:05:11,036
but a lot of people
got swindled.

100
00:05:11,996 --> 00:05:15,596
Even you were misled,
so it seems.

101
00:05:15,636 --> 00:05:19,236
This investigation
is just now getting underway.

102
00:05:19,276 --> 00:05:21,356
And we're gonna need
your cooperation down the road.

103
00:05:21,396 --> 00:05:23,556
Listen...

104
00:05:23,596 --> 00:05:25,516
what's gonna happen
to the people...

105
00:05:25,556 --> 00:05:27,036
who lost their homes?

106
00:05:27,076 --> 00:05:29,956
That'll be up to
the State Liquidation Bureau.

107
00:05:29,996 --> 00:05:31,716
There'll be some kind
of compensation, I imagine...

108
00:05:31,796 --> 00:05:34,636
but nothing like
those policies promised.

109
00:05:34,676 --> 00:05:36,116
And what about this Mr. Nagel?

110
00:05:36,196 --> 00:05:37,796
Any luck with him?

111
00:05:37,836 --> 00:05:40,036
I'm afraid
Mr. Nagel never existed.

112
00:05:41,036 --> 00:05:42,236
But when we pinpoint
who it is...

113
00:05:42,276 --> 00:05:44,236
that was fronting
that operation--

114
00:05:44,276 --> 00:05:46,876
and we do believe
it's someone from your office--

115
00:05:46,916 --> 00:05:48,756
we'll get Mr. Nagel.

116
00:05:48,796 --> 00:05:50,156
It's just a matter of time.

117
00:05:51,316 --> 00:05:52,636
Well...

118
00:05:52,676 --> 00:05:54,596
we would appreciate it
if you'd stick around town...

119
00:05:54,636 --> 00:05:55,876
till this thing's resolved.

120
00:05:55,916 --> 00:05:57,796
Anything I can do to help.

121
00:05:57,836 --> 00:05:58,956
Good.

122
00:06:00,236 --> 00:06:02,756
One more thing.

123
00:06:02,836 --> 00:06:04,516
We'd like it if you'd
turn over your passport...

124
00:06:04,556 --> 00:06:05,716
for the time being.

125
00:06:05,796 --> 00:06:08,156
Of course,
you're under no obligation.

126
00:06:08,236 --> 00:06:09,316
My passport?

127
00:06:09,356 --> 00:06:11,676
That's right.
Won't be needing it...

128
00:06:11,716 --> 00:06:13,196
unless you're planning
on leaving the country.

129
00:06:13,236 --> 00:06:15,876
No, of course not.

130
00:06:15,916 --> 00:06:18,116
Well, good luck
with the investigation.

131
00:07:24,356 --> 00:07:26,156
Jimmy, welcome.

132
00:07:26,196 --> 00:07:27,596
It's been a long time.

133
00:07:27,596 --> 00:07:28,676
Did you get my message?

134
00:07:28,716 --> 00:07:30,756
Yeah. Sure. No trouble at all.

135
00:07:33,196 --> 00:07:35,236
Have you been paid
any money yet?

136
00:07:37,516 --> 00:07:38,636
Neither have I.

137
00:07:38,716 --> 00:07:40,676
I'm gonna level with you.

138
00:07:40,756 --> 00:07:41,796
I think Marvin
has got himself...

139
00:07:41,876 --> 00:07:43,756
into a bit of a jam.

140
00:07:43,796 --> 00:07:44,996
With who?

141
00:07:45,036 --> 00:07:48,036
With Nevesky and the Russians
back in New York.

142
00:07:48,076 --> 00:07:49,316
You didn't know?

143
00:07:50,356 --> 00:07:52,116
They were our partners.

144
00:07:52,156 --> 00:07:53,516
Now they're looking for him.

145
00:07:53,516 --> 00:07:55,436
What's he doing in Cambodia?

146
00:07:55,436 --> 00:07:58,356
Casino.
I don't know much about it.

147
00:07:58,396 --> 00:07:59,756
Right.

148
00:08:00,596 --> 00:08:01,676
There's someone
I want you to meet.

149
00:08:01,716 --> 00:08:02,836
Rocky, come here.

150
00:08:04,236 --> 00:08:05,316
Rocky, this is Jimmy.

151
00:08:05,356 --> 00:08:06,996
Jimmy, this is Rocky.

152
00:08:08,796 --> 00:08:10,076
She's wonderful, isn't she?

153
00:08:12,076 --> 00:08:13,156
Rocky.

154
00:08:21,676 --> 00:08:23,716
We talked about that.

155
00:08:25,276 --> 00:08:26,556
We're engaged to be married.

156
00:08:26,596 --> 00:08:28,836
Congratulations.

157
00:08:28,876 --> 00:08:30,556
She's a bit of a diamond...

158
00:08:30,596 --> 00:08:32,756
in the raw, you know.

159
00:08:32,796 --> 00:08:34,916
I'll make a lady out of her.

160
00:08:34,956 --> 00:08:36,756
You should go up to Chiang Mai.

161
00:08:36,796 --> 00:08:37,876
It's fantastic up there:

162
00:08:37,916 --> 00:08:40,676
bucolic scenery,
cheap guesthouses.

163
00:08:42,636 --> 00:08:44,516
I'm not going up to Chiang Mai.

164
00:08:45,436 --> 00:08:46,596
I'm here to see Marvin.

165
00:08:48,436 --> 00:08:50,236
Well, he won't be expecting you.

166
00:08:50,276 --> 00:08:51,876
Good.

167
00:08:51,916 --> 00:08:54,156
It'll be a surprise.

168
00:08:54,196 --> 00:08:57,116
He'll be glad to see me.
It's been a while.

169
00:08:59,436 --> 00:09:01,316
Well, there's 2 morning flights.

170
00:09:01,356 --> 00:09:02,756
If we don't talk
before you leave...

171
00:09:02,796 --> 00:09:05,476
Iet's meet the day after
tomorrow in Phnom Penh...

172
00:09:05,516 --> 00:09:07,756
at noon, at the Belleville.

173
00:09:07,796 --> 00:09:09,716
They can get you
a room there as well.

174
00:09:23,236 --> 00:09:25,156
-Hello?
-Teddy, it's me--Jimmy.

175
00:09:25,196 --> 00:09:26,276
What's your plan?

176
00:09:26,316 --> 00:09:28,516
I'm flying out first
thing in the morning.

177
00:09:28,556 --> 00:09:29,916
Not so fast.

178
00:09:29,956 --> 00:09:31,596
I had a buddy
check back channels...

179
00:09:31,636 --> 00:09:33,356
with someone in the agency.

180
00:09:33,396 --> 00:09:35,076
The airport
has a security company...

181
00:09:35,116 --> 00:09:37,436
that's plugged
into the embassy...

182
00:09:37,476 --> 00:09:39,996
and your name and passport
are in their system.

183
00:09:40,036 --> 00:09:41,836
-Shit.
-Hey, that's no sweat.

184
00:09:41,876 --> 00:09:43,236
I'll get you across the border.

185
00:09:43,276 --> 00:09:44,876
I live down that way.

186
00:09:44,916 --> 00:09:47,756
Now, there's
an overnight train...

187
00:09:47,796 --> 00:09:50,156
out of Hualampong.

188
00:09:50,196 --> 00:09:51,396
Get you in around 5 a.m.

189
00:09:51,436 --> 00:09:52,756
-Thanks.
-You know where I live?

190
00:09:52,796 --> 00:09:54,236
-Yeah.
-Good.

191
00:09:54,316 --> 00:09:55,556
I'll meet you at the station.

192
00:09:55,596 --> 00:09:56,716
Thanks, Teddy.

193
00:10:33,836 --> 00:10:35,556
We had some great times
in Bangkok--

194
00:10:35,596 --> 00:10:36,676
Marvin and me...

195
00:10:36,716 --> 00:10:39,156
but that was
a lifetime ago, kid.

196
00:10:39,196 --> 00:10:41,196
As the lady says...

197
00:10:41,236 --> 00:10:43,036
I no longer am
what I once was...

198
00:10:43,076 --> 00:10:44,956
nor ever shall be again.

199
00:10:47,356 --> 00:10:49,876
I don't know what
the hell Marvin's up to.

200
00:10:49,956 --> 00:10:52,036
You just be careful.

201
00:10:52,116 --> 00:10:53,756
Something's changed in him.

202
00:10:54,956 --> 00:10:56,396
You can't keep
stealing from Peter...

203
00:10:56,476 --> 00:10:58,516
to pay Paul.

204
00:10:58,556 --> 00:11:01,836
Sooner or later,
Peter gets pissed off.

205
00:11:09,516 --> 00:11:10,916
The main road is off-limits.

206
00:11:10,956 --> 00:11:12,436
There was a French cyclist...

207
00:11:12,476 --> 00:11:14,436
murdered there
about a month ago.

208
00:11:15,916 --> 00:11:17,396
You get waylaid...

209
00:11:18,396 --> 00:11:20,316
you won't be writing
any postcards.

210
00:12:15,916 --> 00:12:17,476
Where you go, sir?

211
00:12:17,516 --> 00:12:18,716
I'm looking for the Belleville.

212
00:12:18,756 --> 00:12:20,236
Yeah. Well, I know.

213
00:12:20,276 --> 00:12:21,596
That's the place right here.
You know this place?

214
00:12:21,636 --> 00:12:22,756
I know, really.

215
00:12:22,796 --> 00:12:25,516
-ls it far from here?
-Not so far. It's over there.

216
00:12:25,556 --> 00:12:27,596
OK. No, thanks.

217
00:12:27,676 --> 00:12:28,836
I got it.

218
00:12:33,076 --> 00:12:35,436
Where you from, sir?

219
00:12:35,436 --> 00:12:36,556
The United States.

220
00:12:36,596 --> 00:12:38,116
Yes. I know very good.

221
00:12:38,156 --> 00:12:39,716
My name Sok.

222
00:12:39,756 --> 00:12:41,596
Sok, Jimmy.

223
00:12:41,636 --> 00:12:42,716
Is this place far?

224
00:12:42,756 --> 00:12:44,716
Not so far.

225
00:12:44,756 --> 00:12:46,636
Don't worry, sir,
I'm a safety driver.

226
00:12:46,636 --> 00:12:47,756
Good.

227
00:12:53,116 --> 00:12:55,556
-This is the Belleville?
-Yeah. Belleville.

228
00:12:58,156 --> 00:12:59,396
I see you took the long way.

229
00:12:59,436 --> 00:13:01,356
Not so long way.

230
00:13:01,396 --> 00:13:02,436
What do I owe you?

231
00:13:02,516 --> 00:13:04,396
No problem. You pay after.

232
00:13:04,396 --> 00:13:05,876
I wait here for you.

233
00:13:05,956 --> 00:13:07,076
-You sure?
-Yeah, sure.

234
00:13:25,516 --> 00:13:26,956
Excuse me.

235
00:13:26,996 --> 00:13:28,076
Yeah?

236
00:13:28,116 --> 00:13:30,996
I'm looking for a guy
named Kaspar.

237
00:13:31,036 --> 00:13:33,756
I don't know everyone
who comes to this place.

238
00:13:33,796 --> 00:13:35,716
-What is your name?
-Jimmy.

239
00:13:35,796 --> 00:13:38,156
Can I get you something?

240
00:13:38,156 --> 00:13:40,516
-A beer.
-Beer.

241
00:13:40,556 --> 00:13:41,796
Jimmy.

242
00:13:50,196 --> 00:13:52,356
Laughing Lotus.

243
00:13:52,396 --> 00:13:54,996
-Beer.
-Thanks.

244
00:13:55,036 --> 00:13:56,196
Hey, man.

245
00:13:57,876 --> 00:14:00,436
You remember me?

246
00:14:00,476 --> 00:14:02,796
-Am I supposed to?
-You look awfully familiar.

247
00:14:02,836 --> 00:14:04,796
Don't we know each other?

248
00:14:04,876 --> 00:14:06,316
I don't think so.

249
00:14:07,676 --> 00:14:09,676
You're Robbie, right?

250
00:14:10,676 --> 00:14:11,956
Nah.

251
00:14:14,556 --> 00:14:15,756
My apologies.

252
00:14:17,196 --> 00:14:19,396
-Excuse me.
-Yeah?

253
00:14:19,436 --> 00:14:20,996
I was told
that you had rooms available.

254
00:14:21,036 --> 00:14:23,036
Yeah.
$5.00 a night with a fan...

255
00:14:23,076 --> 00:14:24,996
and 8.00 with
air conditioning.

256
00:14:25,036 --> 00:14:26,836
OK. I'll take the one
with the air conditioning.

257
00:14:26,876 --> 00:14:28,596
Across the street,
second floor...

258
00:14:28,636 --> 00:14:30,156
bathroom down the hall.

259
00:14:37,836 --> 00:14:39,516
I'd like a beer, Emile.

260
00:14:39,556 --> 00:14:41,156
No. Fuck you, deadbeat.

261
00:14:41,196 --> 00:14:42,756
You still haven't
paid your tab.

262
00:14:42,796 --> 00:14:44,556
-I'm good for it.
-When?!

263
00:14:44,596 --> 00:14:45,996
I got it.

264
00:14:48,956 --> 00:14:50,796
Here, you little shit.

265
00:14:50,796 --> 00:14:52,476
You have a short memory.

266
00:14:52,516 --> 00:14:53,796
Before, you would do
anything I asked.

267
00:14:53,836 --> 00:14:55,876
But lately, you act
as if we have nothing.

268
00:14:55,916 --> 00:14:58,596
It's not an act.
We have nothing.

269
00:14:58,636 --> 00:15:00,396
-You fucking bitch.
-What did you call me?

270
00:15:01,516 --> 00:15:03,076
I call you a fucking bitch...

271
00:15:03,116 --> 00:15:04,236
so fuck off.

272
00:15:06,516 --> 00:15:07,916
What is that in your bag?

273
00:15:07,956 --> 00:15:09,836
-This!
-Hey!

274
00:15:09,836 --> 00:15:12,396
What the fuck is that
doing in your bag--the statue?!

275
00:15:12,436 --> 00:15:13,636
What are you talking about?

276
00:15:13,676 --> 00:15:15,596
You stole it from the wat.

277
00:15:15,636 --> 00:15:18,276
It was you.
I can't fucking believe it.

278
00:15:18,316 --> 00:15:20,596
Hey! Keep your mouth shut.

279
00:15:24,556 --> 00:15:25,956
Hey, I need your passport.

280
00:15:26,996 --> 00:15:29,076
Yes. It's a new law
of the country.

281
00:15:29,116 --> 00:15:30,996
Don't worry. I get you back.

282
00:15:32,556 --> 00:15:34,036
Emile.

283
00:15:36,876 --> 00:15:38,596
Give me the fucking bag.

284
00:15:38,676 --> 00:15:40,076
No way! You stole this!

285
00:15:40,116 --> 00:15:42,276
Leave the fucking bag, OK?

286
00:15:42,316 --> 00:15:43,396
You fucking thief!

287
00:15:45,196 --> 00:15:46,436
Hey!

288
00:15:48,356 --> 00:15:50,436
-Get off me!
-Fucking bitch!

289
00:15:50,476 --> 00:15:51,916
Hey!

290
00:16:05,836 --> 00:16:07,876
Hey, let me take care
of that piece of shit.

291
00:16:30,156 --> 00:16:31,396
Hey!

292
00:16:34,476 --> 00:16:35,556
You piece of shit.

293
00:16:40,516 --> 00:16:43,356
-You sure you're all right?
-Yeah.

294
00:16:43,436 --> 00:16:45,796
-I can't believe this. Thanks.
-You need some ice?

295
00:16:45,876 --> 00:16:46,956
-I'm OK.
-OK?

296
00:16:47,036 --> 00:16:48,516
Yeah.

297
00:16:48,556 --> 00:16:50,316
Thanks for stepping in.
Thanks for your help.

298
00:17:30,156 --> 00:17:31,796
What? Hey!

299
00:17:36,356 --> 00:17:37,476
Hey!

300
00:17:42,116 --> 00:17:43,516
Hey!

301
00:17:43,596 --> 00:17:45,476
How's the room?

302
00:17:45,516 --> 00:17:47,916
What's the matter?
A little hoity-toity for you?

303
00:17:47,996 --> 00:17:49,956
Huh?

304
00:17:49,996 --> 00:17:51,356
I got coupons.

305
00:17:54,636 --> 00:17:57,036
You know a place called
the Laughing Lotus?

306
00:17:58,876 --> 00:17:59,996
It's a brothel...

307
00:18:01,036 --> 00:18:02,236
on the other side of town.

308
00:18:03,436 --> 00:18:05,316
If you like karaoke
and Vietnamese girls...

309
00:18:05,356 --> 00:18:06,876
that place is for you.

310
00:18:08,196 --> 00:18:09,676
Is everything OK with the room?

311
00:18:09,716 --> 00:18:10,796
The room's fine.

312
00:18:10,836 --> 00:18:13,076
I don't remember
requesting a monkey.

313
00:18:13,116 --> 00:18:14,196
Monkey?

314
00:18:14,236 --> 00:18:15,316
-Yeah.
-Where?

315
00:18:15,356 --> 00:18:16,436
In my room--on the terrace...

316
00:18:16,516 --> 00:18:20,156
there was a monkey.

317
00:18:20,196 --> 00:18:22,836
No. You must be mistaken.

318
00:18:22,876 --> 00:18:25,236
There is no monkey
in my hotel. No.

319
00:18:25,316 --> 00:18:26,636
Well, maybe it was a dog...

320
00:18:26,676 --> 00:18:28,636
but it looked an awful
lot like a monkey.

321
00:18:28,676 --> 00:18:31,036
It had hands.

322
00:18:31,116 --> 00:18:33,076
There is no monkey
in my hotel. No.

323
00:18:37,796 --> 00:18:39,316
Everything is OK with the room?

324
00:18:39,356 --> 00:18:41,436
The air conditioner
is on the blink.

325
00:18:41,476 --> 00:18:42,676
It's laying on the floor.

326
00:18:42,716 --> 00:18:45,876
Yes. I'll send you someone
tomorrow morning, you know.

327
00:18:45,916 --> 00:18:47,076
He'll have a look.

328
00:18:51,436 --> 00:18:52,516
My passport.

329
00:18:52,556 --> 00:18:53,756
-Passport?
-Yeah.

330
00:18:53,836 --> 00:18:56,276
-I gave it to you.
-You did?

331
00:18:56,356 --> 00:18:58,476
Don't you remember?
I put it right here on the bar.

332
00:18:58,516 --> 00:18:59,676
I thought you took it back.

333
00:18:59,716 --> 00:19:02,556
I got a friend in Bangkok
who lost his passport.

334
00:19:02,596 --> 00:19:03,676
They put him on the list.

335
00:19:03,716 --> 00:19:05,676
Shut up. You're scaring the man.

336
00:19:05,716 --> 00:19:07,316
No. Wait a minute.

337
00:19:07,356 --> 00:19:10,276
That little cocksucker
you were talking to--

338
00:19:10,316 --> 00:19:11,716
he probably took it.

339
00:19:13,796 --> 00:19:14,916
But, no, don't worry.

340
00:19:14,956 --> 00:19:16,636
He comes here very often,
you know.

341
00:19:16,676 --> 00:19:17,796
I will get it for you.

342
00:19:17,836 --> 00:19:20,236
You don't want to be
on the list. I'm on the list.

343
00:19:22,156 --> 00:19:26,356
Son of a bitch!
Go and don't come back! Go!

344
00:19:33,276 --> 00:19:34,876
Street 213. Laughing Lotus.

345
00:19:34,916 --> 00:19:36,116
Yes, I take you.

346
00:19:36,156 --> 00:19:38,396
Why you go there?
Street 213 no good.

347
00:19:38,436 --> 00:19:39,516
I got to meet someone.

348
00:19:39,556 --> 00:19:41,756
You want to meet someone.

349
00:19:41,796 --> 00:19:43,756
Someday, I buy moto-taxi.

350
00:19:43,796 --> 00:19:45,476
How long have you
been doing this?

351
00:19:45,516 --> 00:19:47,076
Long time.

352
00:19:47,116 --> 00:19:48,716
More than 7 year.

353
00:19:48,756 --> 00:19:51,876
First, I was in the army
in Kampong Thom.

354
00:19:51,916 --> 00:19:54,756
You want to see
my army picture? Here.

355
00:19:59,956 --> 00:20:01,116
How old are you here?

356
00:20:01,156 --> 00:20:03,236
Twenty-eight, 29. Not sure.

357
00:20:03,276 --> 00:20:04,916
-Not sure?
-Yeah.

358
00:20:04,956 --> 00:20:06,516
How come?

359
00:20:06,556 --> 00:20:08,556
Because all my documents
were lost...

360
00:20:08,596 --> 00:20:10,276
during the Khmer Rouge.

361
00:20:10,316 --> 00:20:11,956
After I finish my education...

362
00:20:11,996 --> 00:20:13,836
I went to join to the army...

363
00:20:13,876 --> 00:20:16,516
to fight the Khmer Rouge.

364
00:20:16,556 --> 00:20:18,076
They kill my father...

365
00:20:19,076 --> 00:20:20,836
because he was a doctor.

366
00:20:23,076 --> 00:20:26,076
I do not want them
to kill people again.

367
00:20:26,156 --> 00:20:27,276
What did you say your name was?

368
00:20:27,356 --> 00:20:29,476
Call me Sok.

369
00:20:29,516 --> 00:20:30,596
I'm Jimmy.

370
00:20:39,316 --> 00:20:40,636
Stick around, Sok.

371
00:20:40,676 --> 00:20:41,956
I won't be long.

372
00:20:43,676 --> 00:20:45,396
Hi.

373
00:20:45,436 --> 00:20:46,836
Is this the Laughing Lotus?

374
00:20:46,876 --> 00:20:48,836
Yes. You like yum-yum? Come.

375
00:21:21,516 --> 00:21:24,676
How are you?
Where you come from?

376
00:21:24,716 --> 00:21:26,116
United States.

377
00:21:26,156 --> 00:21:28,836
You'll do all right
with that one, mate.

378
00:21:28,876 --> 00:21:30,716
She'll give you
a run for your money.

379
00:21:30,796 --> 00:21:32,636
This one here, she's my girl.

380
00:21:32,676 --> 00:21:33,836
She's mine.

381
00:21:33,916 --> 00:21:36,476
I'm taking her away from here.

382
00:21:36,516 --> 00:21:39,476
I'm taking her to Battambang,
to beauty school.

383
00:21:39,516 --> 00:21:41,476
In Australia,
I'm putting her in college.

384
00:21:42,516 --> 00:21:43,916
-Beauty school.
-Excuse me, sir.

385
00:21:43,916 --> 00:21:46,396
There's a guy
I'm supposed to meet...

386
00:21:46,436 --> 00:21:48,676
named Marvin.

387
00:21:48,716 --> 00:21:51,636
You see this papasan
over here? He's going down, man.

388
00:21:51,676 --> 00:21:54,556
He's a scumbag.
He's a slave trader.

389
00:21:54,596 --> 00:21:55,756
I'm going to take him out.

390
00:21:55,796 --> 00:21:58,036
I'm gonna have to
take the fucker out.

391
00:21:58,076 --> 00:22:01,636
Fuck it!
Give me a fucking beer...

392
00:22:01,716 --> 00:22:02,916
Papasan!

393
00:22:34,476 --> 00:22:36,396
Hey! Get your hands--
I'm taking her...

394
00:22:41,556 --> 00:22:43,076
I'm taking you
to beauty school.

395
00:22:43,116 --> 00:22:45,836
Get the fuck off me,
you motherfucker...

396
00:24:06,156 --> 00:24:07,236
Hello!

397
00:24:08,276 --> 00:24:09,716
Hello. She fix you.

398
00:24:09,796 --> 00:24:11,876
Bye-bye.

399
00:25:13,916 --> 00:25:15,116
Hey, Sok.

400
00:25:16,276 --> 00:25:17,676
I should have listened to you.

401
00:25:17,756 --> 00:25:21,436
Yeah. That place no good.

402
00:25:21,476 --> 00:25:23,276
Many bad people.

403
00:25:23,316 --> 00:25:25,076
Many bad people, all right.

404
00:25:28,036 --> 00:25:29,436
Why did you take me here?

405
00:25:29,476 --> 00:25:30,876
My house right over there.

406
00:25:30,916 --> 00:25:32,716
Yeah, it's good place.

407
00:25:32,756 --> 00:25:34,636
She's my friend.
She's a doctor.

408
00:25:35,716 --> 00:25:37,796
-How are you feeling?
-I've felt better.

409
00:25:37,836 --> 00:25:41,436
Bye-bye!

410
00:25:41,476 --> 00:25:44,396
Yeah. Yes, they like
to say in English to you.

411
00:25:44,476 --> 00:25:46,196
They think that you like it.

412
00:25:47,276 --> 00:25:49,196
If you want
to stay longer in Cambodia...

413
00:25:49,276 --> 00:25:51,636
you should try
to be away from trouble.

414
00:25:51,676 --> 00:25:53,676
I will try to be
away from trouble.

415
00:25:53,716 --> 00:25:55,436
-Thank you.
-Yes.

416
00:26:05,476 --> 00:26:07,036
Excuse me.

417
00:26:07,076 --> 00:26:10,076
What time did Marvin drop
off that note yesterday?

418
00:26:10,116 --> 00:26:11,516
No, he didn't. It was a Khmer.

419
00:26:11,556 --> 00:26:13,116
He said he worked for Marvin.

420
00:26:13,156 --> 00:26:14,556
Who's looking for Marvin?

421
00:26:16,996 --> 00:26:18,076
A friend of his.

422
00:26:19,196 --> 00:26:20,596
You know where he is?

423
00:26:20,636 --> 00:26:23,396
No. But I know
who he hangs out with--

424
00:26:23,436 --> 00:26:25,796
an ex-general named Sideth...

425
00:26:25,836 --> 00:26:27,956
and that guy Marvin's
way out of his league.

426
00:26:28,916 --> 00:26:30,076
Who are you?

427
00:26:30,116 --> 00:26:31,956
It doesn't matter who I am.

428
00:26:31,996 --> 00:26:33,116
Emile.

429
00:26:36,716 --> 00:26:39,236
You want a piece
of friendly advice?

430
00:26:39,276 --> 00:26:41,156
Go back to wherever
it is you came from...

431
00:26:41,196 --> 00:26:42,636
and leave those people alone.

432
00:26:45,276 --> 00:26:46,396
Salud.

433
00:26:51,716 --> 00:26:54,556
-Who's Sideth?
-A bad guy.

434
00:26:54,636 --> 00:26:56,436
Anybody else come back
here looking for me?

435
00:26:56,476 --> 00:26:58,116
I haven't seen anyone.

436
00:26:58,156 --> 00:27:00,276
You know, things run
on a different clock here.

437
00:27:00,316 --> 00:27:02,516
My clock stopped
when a B-40 rocket...

438
00:27:02,556 --> 00:27:04,756
hit my jeep in Mondolkiri.

439
00:27:04,796 --> 00:27:06,116
Really?

440
00:27:06,156 --> 00:27:07,916
I still got shrapnel in my neck.

441
00:27:10,196 --> 00:27:11,316
You can see it.

442
00:27:12,876 --> 00:27:13,996
Look.

443
00:27:18,036 --> 00:27:19,716
I don't see anything.

444
00:27:25,516 --> 00:27:27,876
Maybe you need
a pair of glasses.

445
00:27:32,556 --> 00:27:34,996
He calls himself
"the man of contradictions."

446
00:27:35,036 --> 00:27:36,836
But he's a little bit...

447
00:27:36,876 --> 00:27:39,076
This place attract them
like flies.

448
00:27:40,236 --> 00:27:43,116
Yes. I have Calvados
from my country.

449
00:27:43,156 --> 00:27:44,996
-Thanks.
-Have a glass.

450
00:27:50,476 --> 00:27:53,316
-What's her story?
-Sophie?

451
00:27:54,596 --> 00:27:56,636
No offense,
but guys like you and me--

452
00:27:56,716 --> 00:27:58,516
we don't stand a chance.

453
00:27:58,556 --> 00:28:00,876
No offense, but...

454
00:28:00,916 --> 00:28:02,516
speak for yourself.

455
00:28:13,476 --> 00:28:15,076
Excuse me.

456
00:28:15,116 --> 00:28:17,316
-What?
-Those are my glasses.

457
00:28:17,356 --> 00:28:20,356
Here. $5.00.
Get yourself a new pair.

458
00:28:21,516 --> 00:28:24,596
I'll take these back. Thanks.

459
00:28:31,636 --> 00:28:33,196
Hi.

460
00:28:33,236 --> 00:28:34,996
Thank you so much for--

461
00:28:35,036 --> 00:28:36,476
What happened to your eye?

462
00:28:37,676 --> 00:28:40,276
I was in the wrong place
at the wrong time.

463
00:28:40,316 --> 00:28:42,036
Yeah. You seem like that type.

464
00:28:43,236 --> 00:28:44,356
Which type?

465
00:28:44,396 --> 00:28:47,116
The wrong place,
wrong time type.

466
00:28:47,156 --> 00:28:49,196
I guess that makes two of us.

467
00:28:49,236 --> 00:28:50,636
-Please.
-Sophie.

468
00:28:50,676 --> 00:28:52,876
Gonna introduce us
to your friend?

469
00:28:52,916 --> 00:28:57,036
-Jimmy.
-Hi. Sabrina. Robbie.

470
00:28:57,116 --> 00:28:58,516
So this is for you.

471
00:28:59,596 --> 00:29:03,836
So are you free for...

472
00:29:03,916 --> 00:29:04,996
tonight for dinner?

473
00:29:05,036 --> 00:29:07,076
You know, I can't.
I've got plans tonight.

474
00:29:09,436 --> 00:29:10,756
We should go.
We're gonna be late.

475
00:29:12,596 --> 00:29:14,076
Come on, Robbie.

476
00:29:32,396 --> 00:29:33,836
You weren't on the plane.

477
00:29:40,236 --> 00:29:42,516
Wow. That's a new look for you.

478
00:29:42,556 --> 00:29:43,956
You like it?

479
00:29:43,996 --> 00:29:45,116
I can fix you up for one.

480
00:29:47,876 --> 00:29:50,156
-What happened?
-I got popped.

481
00:29:50,196 --> 00:29:52,836
-By who?
-I don't know.

482
00:29:52,876 --> 00:29:54,756
Well, you should be grateful
money's all they wanted.

483
00:29:55,916 --> 00:29:57,476
You're lucky one of your kidneys
isn't lying...

484
00:29:57,516 --> 00:29:59,916
at the bottom
of somebody's ice chest.

485
00:29:59,956 --> 00:30:01,676
They didn't take my money.

486
00:30:07,356 --> 00:30:09,436
Does Marvin know
where I'm staying?

487
00:30:09,476 --> 00:30:11,716
Well, you can ask him
when you see him.

488
00:30:29,196 --> 00:30:30,676
I hate this country.

489
00:30:44,836 --> 00:30:46,356
Hey, Jimmy boy.

490
00:30:55,836 --> 00:30:57,196
It's good to see you.

491
00:30:57,236 --> 00:30:59,196
So, come on.

492
00:30:59,276 --> 00:31:03,476
What do you think of the layout?

493
00:31:05,116 --> 00:31:06,396
You know,

494
00:31:06,476 --> 00:31:08,436
this is the old
governor's residence.

495
00:31:14,236 --> 00:31:15,676
Do you like it?

496
00:31:15,756 --> 00:31:17,716
It could do with
a fresh coat of paint.

497
00:31:18,876 --> 00:31:21,196
The whole country
needs a paint job.

498
00:31:21,236 --> 00:31:22,956
But that's part of its charm.

499
00:31:22,996 --> 00:31:25,436
Yeah.

500
00:31:25,476 --> 00:31:26,836
I need to talk to Jimmy alone...

501
00:31:26,876 --> 00:31:28,116
for a second.

502
00:31:28,156 --> 00:31:29,716
You want to wait outside?

503
00:31:29,756 --> 00:31:31,236
Yeah. Sure.

504
00:31:35,636 --> 00:31:38,476
That was some place
you sent me to yesterday.

505
00:31:38,516 --> 00:31:40,996
-I got your note.
-What note?

506
00:31:43,156 --> 00:31:44,836
The one you left
at the Belleville.

507
00:31:46,316 --> 00:31:48,236
I didn't leave you any note.

508
00:32:16,236 --> 00:32:19,716
-What are you doing here?
-I thought you wanted to see me.

509
00:32:19,756 --> 00:32:22,436
-I what?
-I thought you wanted to see me.

510
00:32:22,476 --> 00:32:23,876
I'll call you
if I want to see you.

511
00:32:25,356 --> 00:32:27,276
-Go.
-Good-bye.

512
00:32:28,636 --> 00:32:30,756
I have them boil everything--
food, water...

513
00:32:30,796 --> 00:32:32,516
even the bed sheets
and the tablecloth.

514
00:32:32,556 --> 00:32:34,996
85% of the people
on the planet are infested...

515
00:32:35,036 --> 00:32:36,756
with some kind
of microscopic bug.

516
00:32:36,796 --> 00:32:39,076
Now, with stats like that...

517
00:32:39,116 --> 00:32:40,716
you know
you can't be too careful.

518
00:32:46,636 --> 00:32:47,716
You were supposed to stay put...

519
00:32:47,796 --> 00:32:49,836
until you heard from me.

520
00:32:51,196 --> 00:32:53,316
Yeah, well...

521
00:32:53,356 --> 00:32:55,076
The Feds were all over me.

522
00:32:56,196 --> 00:32:57,476
I had to get away.

523
00:32:59,516 --> 00:33:01,236
Forget it. Spilled milk.

524
00:33:01,276 --> 00:33:03,876
And you did an excellent job.

525
00:33:03,916 --> 00:33:07,036
-I'm very proud of you, Jimmy.
-Thanks.

526
00:33:07,076 --> 00:33:08,316
To tell you the truth,

527
00:33:08,356 --> 00:33:10,916
I think in some ways
you're better off here.

528
00:33:10,956 --> 00:33:12,756
I mean, this place is wide open.

529
00:33:12,796 --> 00:33:14,436
A fortune to be made.

530
00:33:14,516 --> 00:33:17,276
You are gonna want
to be a part of it.

531
00:33:17,316 --> 00:33:20,596
Yeah, well, I'm not so sure,
not after the last one.

532
00:33:20,636 --> 00:33:23,316
We really sold
those people a bad deal.

533
00:33:23,356 --> 00:33:24,836
If I had to do it
